Introduction 
Allows teachers to manipulate absences and tardies and notify students if they have too much missed class time
Allows students to view absences 
Teachers are the primary users, as they can manipulate the absences but students have the ability to view their absences as well 
The primary goal is to allow the teacher to take attendance and then alert the teachers and students if a student is late too many times to allow the student to meet with the teacher. 
Overall description 
The class Dean, extends Faculty Member
The Dean holds a list of teachers and views their respective students total missed class time
The Dean can increase a teacher's salary and give teachers warnings
	* These serve as incentives for teachers
Developed by students in Object Oriented Software Development at DePauw University and is intended to be used by anyone wanting to use an absence counter 
Will potentially include: graphical interface
This is designed to work with Java and users can run it on Windows, Mac, or Linux
Will include a user’s guide and simple help for any issues 
External Interface Requirements
The software will need to run on a desktop or laptop
Only needs to interface with the java platform 



Use Cases for Absence Counter

Use Case #1: Student hits the maximum amount of missed class time, based off of the cap the teaher selects.
The teacher clicks on the GUI representation of absences for the student
Teacher adds one absence to the student’s absence counter
Teacher clicks submit 
The computer checks the number of absences the student has for the 30 submission period
The computer sees that the student has gone over the maximum number of allowed absences 
The computer sends a notification to the teacher alerting them that a student is over the maximum number of allowed absences
The computer sends a notification to the teacher alerting them that a student is over the maximum number of allowed absences
Use Case #2: Teacher accidentally adds an absence to the wrong student
Teacher clicks on the GUI representation of Search method 
Teacher types in the student’s ID number
Computer iterates through all ID numbers in the database until it finds a match
Computer returns student’s information
Teacher reduces the number of absences for the student by 1
Teacher saves the changes
Computer removes one absence from the absence counter of the student

Use Case #3: Secretary mistypes ID number when checking in
Secretary types the student’s ID number 
Computer iterates through the list of student ID numbers until a match is found
Computer does not find a match
Computer returns an error message stating no match was found


